        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb 20</date>
                    <salute>Dear Mr Wilson</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Many thanks for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> note.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I rec<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> a letter the other day from D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Müller on the same subject, &amp; from his kindness &amp; yours, I shall receive more answer from Australia than from any other quarter of the world.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> This is a great piece of good fortune, as the Australians are I suppose nearly the most distinct of all races. This reminds me to ask you whether you happen to possess any moderately large photographs of Australians; In this case if you w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> lend them to me for a day or 2 I w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> send for them. I have a considerable collection, but it contains no Australian &amp; I should like to compare them.<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>Pray believe me | yours very faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5896.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Edward Wilson, 19 February 1868</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5896.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Edward Wilson, 19 February 1868</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD had enclosed a copy of his queries on expression with a <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5424.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Ferdinand von Mueller, 28 February [1867]</ref> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 15; see also <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5677.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Samuel Wilson to Ferdinand von Mueller, 12 November 1867</ref>). Mueller’s letter to CD has not been found.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">CD’s surviving collection of photographs on expression is in the Darwin Archive and Darwin Library–CUL (DAR 53.1). It includes a set of prints of non-European peoples from the Museum de Paris.</note>
        </div>        
            
